element.name: Forge and Tower by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)

long-description.p: The old forge dates back to the 1850's it has gable-fronted single-bay single-storey with a horseshoe shaped entrance.also nearby is a former Presbyterian church, which has a Two-bay side elevation to nave and a square profiled four-stage castellated bell tower. The Church is set in a graveyard which is now privately owned and disused.

This is a simple cache and dash at the above coords.
please take care where you park as this is a busy road.
